---
id: org.dxos.introspect-mcp
name: IntrospectMcp
version: 0.1.0
extends: [org.dxos.introspect@0.1.0]
---

MCP server that exposes `@dxos/introspect` over stdio. A thin adapter: tool
schema definitions, parameter validation, response shaping for token budgets,
and stable ref formatting. All real logic lives in the core package.

## Extensions

| Term      | URI                          |
| --------- | ---------------------------- |
| `type`    | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`      |
| `op`      | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`        |
| `service` | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`   |
| `feat`    | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`      |
| `test`    | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`      |

## Types

```mdl
type ToolResult
  desc: Shape returned by every tool — a JSON envelope with optional truncation note.
  fields:
    data:       any
    note?:      string                  # explanation when data is null
    truncated?: string                  # summary of dropped results when capped
```

```mdl
type ServerOptions
  fields:
    introspector: Introspector          # see org.dxos.introspect
    name?:        string                # MCP server name advertised to clients
    version?:     string
    logger?:      ToolLogger
```

## Services

```mdl
service McpServer
  desc: |
    Wraps `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` McpServer. Boots over stdio (default)
    or HTTP (later). Connects an Introspector to four tools mapped to its
    query methods.
  loading: eager
  ops:
    create(options: ServerOptions) → McpServer
    connect(transport: Transport) → Promise<void>
    close() → Promise<void>
  requires: [Introspector]
```

## Operations (MCP Tools)

```mdl
op list_packages
  desc: |
    List packages in the DXOS monorepo. Use this to discover what packages
    exist before drilling into one.
  input:
    name?:        string                # substring of the package name
    pathPrefix?:  string                # e.g. "packages/plugins"
    privateOnly?: boolean
  output: ToolResult                    # data: Package[]
  note: response capped at 30 entries; surplus reported via `truncated`
```

```mdl
op get_package
  desc: Fetch the full record for a single package by exact name.
  input:
    name: string                        # e.g. "@dxos/echo"
  output: ToolResult                    # data: PackageDetail | null
```

```mdl
op find_symbol
  desc: |
    Find an exported symbol by name or partial name across all DXOS
    packages. Returns refs that can be passed to `get_symbol`.
  input:
    query: string
    kind?: SymbolKind
  output: ToolResult                    # data: SymbolMatch[]
  note: ranking — exact > prefix > substring; capped at 30
```

```mdl
op get_symbol
  desc: |
    Fetch detail for a single symbol by ref (e.g. "@dxos/echo#Expando").
    Default: signature + JSDoc summary + source location.
    Pass `include=['source']` for the full declaration text.
  input:
    ref:      string                    # <package>#<name>
    include?: ('source' | 'jsdoc' | 'signature')[]
  output: ToolResult                    # data: SymbolDetail | null
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Tool surface

  req F-1.1:
    when: an MCP client lists tools
    then: exactly four tools are advertised — list_packages, get_package, find_symbol, get_symbol

  req F-1.2:
    when: a tool description is read by an LLM
    then: it specifies *when* to use the tool, not just what it does
    note: drives trigger accuracy; generic descriptions are an anti-pattern
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Response shaping

  req F-2.1:
    when: a list response would exceed 30 entries
    then: response is capped and `truncated` carries a refinement hint

  req F-2.2:
    when: get_symbol is called without `include`
    then: response omits `source` and full `jsdoc`; only signature + summary returned

  req F-2.3:
    when: source or JSDoc preview exceeds the budget (1.2kB / 600B)
    then: text is truncated with a marker indicating remaining length

  req F-2.4:
    when: a record-fetch tool (get_package / get_symbol) finds nothing
    then: data is null and `note` explains which key was missing
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Tool-call observability

  req F-3.1:
    when: a logger is configured via ServerOptions
    then: every tool call is recorded with tool name, args, and response shape

  req F-3.2:
    when: future search_code tool is added (later phase)
    then: its calls are logged separately so unmatched queries can drive new structured tools
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Tool surface contract
  given: server connected to a fixture introspector
  when: client calls listTools
  then: returned tool names sorted equal ['find_symbol', 'get_package', 'get_symbol', 'list_packages']
```

```mdl
test T-2: list_packages name filter
  given: server connected to fixture monorepo with pkg-a and pkg-b
  when: client calls list_packages with arguments { name: 'pkg-a' }
  then: data.map(p => p.name) === ['@fixture/pkg-a']
```

```mdl
test T-3: find_symbol surfaces ECHO Task
  given: server connected
  when: client calls find_symbol with query 'Task'
  then:
    - some result has ref '@fixture/pkg-a#Task'
    - that result's summary contains 'Task item'
```

```mdl
test T-4: get_symbol expands source on demand
  given: server connected
  when: client calls get_symbol with { ref: '@fixture/pkg-a#Task', include: ['source'] }
  then:
    - data.source contains 'Schema.Struct'
    - data.source contains 'Type.object'
    - data.source contains 'com.example.type.Task'
```

```mdl
test T-5: Unknown ref returns null with note
  given: server connected
  when: client calls get_symbol with { ref: '@fixture/pkg-a#nonexistent' }
  then:
    - data is null
    - note contains 'No symbol'
```

